answer:
1. Cut the four upper fingers of the glove in latex so as to leave the thumb intact.
2. Cut a piece of 30cm. silicone tube (see FASE 1);
3. Take the just cut glove and insert it into the larger beaker of 250ml. using a piece of paper tape to ensure that it is sealed. Then insert the silicone tube into the glove and secure it with a plastic clip (see FASE 2);
4. Insert the free end of the silicone tube into the U-shaped distillation tube. Also in this case secure everything with a piece of paper tape (see FASE 3);
5. Position the pliers and the plastic base so that you can support the smaller beaker of 100ml. in one of the two pliers, then place the U-shaped distillation tube inside it, closing its free end with a rubber stopper (see FASE 4);
6. Move back to the larger beaker of 250ml. and cut the thumb from the tip. Use the thermometer to measure the temperature of the solution.
7. When the temperature of the solution reaches 65°C, the alcohol contained in the mixture begins to evaporate and flows through the silicone tube to the U-shaped distillation tube, where it condenses due to the surface cooled by the ice present in the beaker.
8. During the entire process of extracting alcohol from the mixture, the temperature measured with the thermometer will remain constant, its rise will therefore indicate the end of the alcohol in the mixture.
